description: Human Bronchial Fibroblasts (HBF) from ScienCell Research Laboratories are isolated from human bronchus tissue.  They resemble a mesenchymal stem cell phenotype and their principle function is the production of type III collagen, elastin, and proteoglycans of the extracellular matrix.
note: Ordered as Total RNA. RNA isolation procedure excludes RNAs < 200 nucleotides.
